THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF NEVADA, REPRESENTED IN
SENATE AND ASSEMBLY, DO ENACT AS FOLLOWS:
1 Section 1. NRS 408.656 is hereby amended to read as follows:
2 408.656 1. The Wildlife Crossings Account is hereby created
3 in the State General Fund. The Director shall administer the
4 Account. The Account is a continuing account without reversion.
5 2. [Any] All money credited to the Account from the fee
6 imposed pursuant to NRS 444A.090 and any proceeds from the
7 issuance of bonds or other securities for the Account must be
8 deposited in the State Treasury for credit to the Account.
9 3. The Director may accept gifts, grants and bequests of money
10 from any public or private source. The money must be deposited in
11 the State Treasury for credit to the Account.
12 4. Money in the Account must be used by the Department for
13 the design, construction, identification, restoration and protection of
14 wildlife crossings and other related highway features to improve
15 wildlife permeability in this State, which may include, without
16 limitation:
17 (a) Matching any federal money for a project to design,
18 construct, identify, restore or protect wildlife crossings and other
19 related highway features;
20 (b) Conducting studies on wildlife crossings and other related
21 highway features;
22 (c) Designing or constructing wildlife crossings and other
23 related highway features;
24 (d) Planning related to wildlife crossings and other related
25 highway features;
26 (e) Staffing needs related to the design, construction,
27 identification, restoration and protection of wildlife crossings and
28 other related highway features; and
29 (f) Carrying out the provisions of NRS 408.651 to 408.676,
30 inclusive, in cooperation with the Department of Wildlife.
31 5. In administering the Account, the Department shall consult
32 with the Department of Wildlife to:
33 (a) Identify locations where key wildlife habitat, wildlife
34 migration corridors and highways intersect;
35 (b) Identify and implement strategies to avoid, minimize and
36 mitigate wildlife-vehicle collisions; and
37 (c) Prioritize areas to implement projects for wildlife crossings
38 or other related highway features to improve permeability for
39 wildlife while maintaining highway user safety.
40 6. All claims against the Account must be paid as other claims
41 against the State are paid.
