1 Sec. 2. NRS 444A.090 is hereby amended to read as follows:
2 444A.090 1. A person who sells a new tire for a vehicle to a
3 customer for any purpose other than for resale by the customer in
4 the ordinary course of business shall collect from the purchaser at
5 the time the person collects the applicable sales taxes for the sale a
6 fee of [$1] $2 per tire. A person who did not pay the fee imposed by
7 this section at the time of purchase because he or she purchased the
8 new tire for resale and who then makes any use of that tire other
9 than to resell it in the ordinary course of business, shall pay the fee
10 imposed by this section to the Department of Taxation at the time of
11 the first use of that tire for a purpose other than holding it for resale.
12 2. The seller shall account separately for all money received
13 pursuant to subsection 1 as a deposit to be held in trust for the State.
14 In accordance with the regulations adopted pursuant to subsection 3,
15 the seller shall transmit 95 percent of the money held in trust
16 pursuant to this section to the Department of Taxation for deposit
17 with the State Treasurer . [for] The State Treasurer shall credit half
18 of the money transmitted pursuant to this subsection to the
19 Wildlife Crossings Account created by NRS 408.656 in the State
20 General Fund and half of the money to the Solid Waste
21 Management Account in the State General Fund. The remaining 5
22 percent and all interest and income which accrued on the money
23 while in trust with the seller become the property of the seller on the
24 day the balance for the month is transmitted to the Department of
25 Taxation and may be retained by the seller to cover his or her related
26 administrative costs.
27 3. The Director of the Department of Taxation shall adopt
28 regulations establishing acceptable methods for accounting for and
29 transmitting to the Department money collected or required to be
30 paid by retailers pursuant to subsection 1. The regulations must
31 include a designation of the persons responsible for payment. The
32 regulations must, in appropriate situations, allow for the
33 transmission of that money together with the payment of the
34 applicable sales and use taxes.
35 4. In collecting the fee, the Department of Taxation may
36 employ any administrative and legal powers conferred upon it for
37 the collection of the sales and use taxes by chapters 360 and 372 of
38 NRS.
39 5. The fee imposed pursuant to subsection 1 does not apply to
40 any tire included in the sale of a new or used vehicle unless the tire
41 is sold in a separate transaction.
42 Sec. 3. This act becomes effective on July 1, 2025.
